free_txt: SD: Institute code updated. Small
corrections in all Subents.
in French
Four surface barrier detectors with the
thickness of 50 mm2 were used. Three detectors could
rotate from 21.5 up to 158.5 degr. They were located
at a distance of 130 mm from the center of a gas
chamber. Fourth detector located at an angle of 165
degrees was used as the monitor.
Gas target from a natural neon (90.5% 20Ne) with
different pumping was used.
Fig.2 from Nucl.Phys.,A112(1968)161
Errors from the graphic bars include
statistical errors and uncertainty in pressure,
purity of the target, beam intensity and energy,
dead time, etc.)
